  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Until now, diagnosis of constriction was based on pressure changes of ventricle by
      conventional pressure-wide hemodynamic evaluation but not on ventricular volume change. This
      study will provide answers to persisting questions about volume changes during respiration in
      patients with constrictive pericarditis by directly measuring both right and left ventricular
      volume.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
